overview: The user wanted to improve the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. I began by thoroughly
  reviewing the existing design, identifying areas like the color palette,
  layout, and form elements that needed refinement. The approach involved
  implementing a new calming, sleep-themed color palette, redesigning the main
  form layout with subtle background elements and an improved progress
  indicator, and enhancing all core UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, and sliders. A significant part of the effort was dedicated to
  applying consistent styling across all questionnaire sections, transforming
  plain gray boxes into cohesive, themed card-like groupings. Finally, I
  addressed a console error where input fields were receiving null values, by
  modifying the Input component to safely handle these. The outcome is a much
  more polished, professional, and thematically appropriate application.
